I}}\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=Bug|type2=Steel}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=II}}\n{{Spritebox/2|ndex=212}}\n{{Spritebox/3|ndex=212}}\n{{Spritebox/4/Gender|ndex=212}}\n{{Spritebox/5/Gender|ndex=212}}\n{{Spritebox/6/2FormsGender|ndex=212|form1=M}}\n{{Spritebox/7/2FormsGender|ndex=212|form1=M}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|212|Scizor}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Scizor shares its {{pkmn|category}} with {{p|Kingler}}. They are both known as the Pincer Pokémon (though Scizor was known as the Scissors Pokémon in [[Generation II]] and has been called the Scissor Pokémon in the {{pkmn|anime}}).\n* Despite having different base stats, Scizor and {{p|Scyther|its pre-evolved form}} both have a base stat total of 500. In turn, Scizor is the only Pokémon to not have its base stat total changed upon evolving.\n* Mega Scizor is tied with {{me|Pinsir}}, Mega {{p|Heracross}}, and {{p|Genesect}} for the highest base stat total of all {{type|Bug}} Pokémon.\n* Scizor and Scyther, along with Pinsir, are the only Pokémon legitimately available in all 27 in-game [[Poké Ball]] variants.\n* Scizor can be seen as a parallel to {{p|Steelix}}. They both have pre-evolved forms from [[Generation I]], and both evolve via trading with a [[Metal Coat]] in which both lose a typing to gain the {{t|Steel}} type.\n\n===Origin===\nScizor shares characteristics with flying {{wp|Fire ant|red ants}} and {{wp|mantis}}es. It also shares characteristics with {{wp|wasp}}-mimicking {{wp|Mantispidae|mantidflies}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nScizor is a corruption of \'\'{{wp|scissors|scissor}}\'\' or a combination of \'\'scissors\'\' and \'\'{{wp|razor}}\'\'.\n\nHassam is a corruption of 剪む \'\'hasamu\'\' (to clip or snip).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Bug|type2=Steel\n|ja=ハッサム \'\'Hassam\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|剪む \'\'hasamu\'\'|clip, snip}}\n|fr=Cizayox|frmeaning=From a corruption of \'\'{{tt|ciseaux|scissors}}\'\', and possibly \'\'oxidation\'\', in reference to its rust-red color\n|es=Scizor|esmeaning=Same as English 